bat, I would like to know if I need to modify my tactics.<br><br>Using these tactics I can take 6 spider spawns as well as the &quot;slave&quot; spawn that is in the middle of the spider area before I have start the cycle over again, downtime is almost nill unless I get a particularly bad spider.  I had been toying with rooting one to single pull them, but it seems to be faster when I just go with two and slow the one I didn't pull first during battle.  I take a beating, sure, but I got a Druid so it's all good.  I average about 4 blue exp an hour. <p>Skraach Katfevr<br>41 Vah Shir Beastlord<br>Prexus<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=142640" TARGET="_blank">My Crap</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ubukudahoesmakker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Buku Da Hoesmakker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR color=#330066><CENTER>Beast Overlord</CENTER><HR color=#330066></span><br>  Posts: 523<br> <font color=#871F78>(5/30/02 7:09:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1717.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bukar.freeservers.com/Bukarsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you use during battle?</span><hr size=1> To see if your pet is outdamaging you just run a log parsing program. I used one quite a bit early on when I was trying to come up with a good strategy.  <p><BR><img src="http://photo.msn.s8.com/MS8zLzAvMS8xMDg2LzE1NS8zMi9JVXEtdGJkd2lqYWxaZGtBVFFSbXN3/4769be8b7ffb4dae0cfa5767b5c414e1/clbk=*EtEZjHm6cpOeiq3enA6P9Iz69VVtD53t1dUzGtkIESkEcGvsdFwm93Bzx0wqUKq587WMzJOAik$/jpg.jpg"><BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=118708 ">Bukar Tigerclaw</a><